Why CC-BY-SA for the profiles?

The voice profiles in this repo describe how communities of writers handle
register, rhythm, lexis, and discourse. They are working hypotheses, not finished
products. CC-BY-SA exists so that when a community improves a profile that
describes them, the improvement remains available — under the same terms — to
the next person who needs it.

If you fork a profile:

  - Keep the citations.
  - Mark your version as a fork and credit the previous author(s).
  - License your version CC-BY-SA 4.0.

If you write a new profile from scratch using this schema, you can license it
however you want, but we suggest CC-BY-SA so the ecosystem stays interoperable.

